Citations
Date: 0/0/1965
Source: High Endeavour
Author: VANCE
Vol / Page: 51
Edition:
Quote: Sometimes shearers had to ford flooded rivers so as to be at an 'open shed' station on time. 'Open shed' stations picked their shearers from those present when the shed opened; there were no prior engagements and no jobs for latecomers.
Notes:

